name: lifelines
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "lifelines" %}
{% set version = "0.9.4" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  md5: fcc5b45d1030edafab242db639ef74eb

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools

  run:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - numpy
    - scipy
    - pandas >=0.18

test:
  imports:
    - lifelines
    - lifelines.datasets
    - lifelines.fitters
    - lifelines.utils

about:
  home: https://github.com/CamDavidsonPilon/lifelines
  license: MIT
  summary: 'Survival analysis in Python, including Kaplan Meier, Nelson Aalen and regression'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - mariusvniekerk
    - CamDavidsonPilon

about.summary: Survival analysis in Python, including Kaplan Meier, Nelson Aalen and regression
